    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Posts used to mark the location of a grave and in commemoration of the deceased; known in many cultures. They were originally made of a single timber, often decorated with totemic emblems or other iconography. Grave posts may also be made of materials other than wood, but in form resemble the tall, verticality of a tree trunk. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
